description: **Manufacturing process**These little dragon figures are unique, which means that there is only one copy of each figure.From the thought of a small sleeping dragon wrapping around a crystal, I couldn't help but realize it.I modeled each of these little dragons by hand and baked them together with the rock crystals in the oven.After the figures have cooled down, I carefully removed the rock crystals.Afterwards, each dragon was individually painted with acrylic lacquer paints.The colors are waterproof and scratchy, but in order to protect them again for safety reasons, I covered the entire figures again with a silk matt gloss lacquer.This is how the Little Dragonscleaned with water and a soft cloth if necessary.When the paint was completely dried, I was able to put the crystals back into their socket and attach them using epoxy resin glue.Finally, fabric dresses were glued onto the undersides.**Size**The individual dragons all have a slightly different sizeRed/Green Dragon:H= 50 B= 60 L= 60Blue Dragon:H= 50 B= 55 L= 55Yellow/Pink Dragon:H= 45 B= 50 L= 50**Material**- Polymerclay (Super Sculpey)- Rock crystals- Epoxy resin adhesive- Acrylic lacquer gloss colours- Silk matt gloss lacquer

name: Cotton necklace with a Maori Twist pendant
description: Manufacturing process:The pendant was sawn by hand from a precious wood panel.After that, it was brought into the right shape with various milling, filings and engraving stitches.The edges were then finely ground. The trailer was then treated with a hard wax oil and carefully polished.Towards the end, a new cotton cord in the color of your choice is braided by hand and connected to the pendant.You can determine the length of the tape yourself by means of an adjustable knot closure.-------------------------------------------Symbol Meaning of the pendant:**Pikorua (Twist)**The Maori Twist symbol is a very popular symbol because of its meaning.Pikorua, as the Twist symbol is called in Maori, stands for the bond between two people, whether through friendship, love or blood.The Twist symbol also resembles the way of life and eternity. In this context, it refers to the eternal bond between two people that will never fade, even if these individuals are separated for short or long periods of time and as they will always be together. That's why the Maori Twist symbol pendant is a very popular gift among lovers, family, friends and even in situations when someone has died.**Material**- Hardwood- Cotton cord
